The paper proposes a method for neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning and deep learning. The method involves constructing a super network and assigning architecture weights to candidate operations, which suggests a focus on optimization and training of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) are also possible sub-categories, but less likely given the focus on image classification tasks in the experiments.
